A total number of 2000 Police officers will give security when President Muhammadu Buhari visit Nasarawa State on Wednesday. The police officers and men will work under the supervision of the Commissioner of Police in charge of Nasarawa Command, Mr. Bola E. Longe. The Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Samaila Usman said: “The police has put on the mechanisms to make the visit smooth by the provision of Mobil Police, Counter Terrorism Unit, Intelligence Personnel, Mounted Troop, Explosive Ordinance Disposal and Conventional Police Officers. “All the officers have been briefed and will apply professionalism.” Police personnel grumble over non-payment of salaries, deductions Nasarawa gets new police commissioner, Muhammad Kura Police station 2,050 men as Buhari arrives Plateau